DOMTextRun.characters: We recommend that the patient receives emergency surgery. Analysis of the CT scans of the patient's head show a gray, crescent-shaped appearance just under the skull on five adjacent scans. This indicates that there is a subdural hematoma on the right side of the head near the temporal lobe. Surgery should be performed because if the blood remains or continues to collect in the head, the hematoma will increase pressure within the skull and cause additional brain damage.
